SIMPLE: contrite
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contrite
<hw>Con"trite</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>contritus</ets> bruised, p. p. of <ets>contrere</ets> to grind,
bruise; <ets>con-</ets> + <ets>terere</ets> to rub, grind: cf. F.
<ets>contrit</ets> See <er>Trite</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Thoroughly bruised or broken.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Broken down with grief and penitence; deeply
sorrowful for sin because it is displeasing to God; humbly and
thoroughly penitent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>contrite</qex> heart, O God, thou wilt not despise.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. li. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be penitent, and for thy fault <qex>contrite</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Penitent; repentant; humble; sorrowful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Contrite
<hw>Con"trite</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contrite person.</def>
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Contrite
<hw>Con"trite</hw>, <pos>v.</pos> <def>In a contrite manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contriteness</ent>⟦br⟧
